Hoth: Echo Med Lab (v)<br />
Rendezvous Point   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <b>Responses to reviews</b><br />
<br />
vs big blue you should be able to occupy at least one system (usually hoth, with haven, until you have to run away when they have 90 power!), just remember to keep a jedi on a ship to stop overwhelmed. But if they&#39;ve got green cards it&#39;s a big problem with the heavy reliance on capitals. If you can at least occupy that system you should be ok as you disrupt their game plan, hold battle plan and drain at the 3rd/4th marker.<br />
<br />
@Patrick. YOu can always be counted on to give a helpful review.<br />
<br />
@Jonathan. I do start the system, I just put Hoth in the wrong column.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Strategy</b><br />
<br />
This deck sets up pretty much the same every game:<br />
<br />
<b>1st turn</b><br />
<ul><li>Opponent&#39;s turn - pull Rieken (v)<br />
<li>Start of your turn - pull 2 echo sites (usually war room and med lab) with ANSB and General McQuarrie<br />
<li>Deploy sites (make sure war room is furthest from exterior sites), rieken to war room, mcquarrie to site closest to exterior sites.<br />
<li>Pull hoth sentry with rieken (v) and put it on the 4th marker.<br />
<li>Deploy Sai&#39;tor (v) if it&#39;s there and you have a jedi in hand.<br />
<li>Draw/save depending on what&#39;s in hand</ul><br />
<br />
<b>2nd Turn</b><br />
<ul><li>Start of your turn - decide if you want to go to space or ground. This will depend on hand and matchup.<br />
<li>If <b>space</b>, you want to set up EBO so you need to pull either 3rd echo site or EBO with ANSB.<br />
<li>If you have drawn any of corporal delevar, tigran (v), an echo site or EBO by now then you can get EBO out this turn. If not, then you will have to download one of them with Rieken (v) (he can pull the corridor if necessary) and pull the last piece of the puzzle next turn.<br />
<li>If <b>ground</b>, then pull rendezvous point/endor for more generation.<br />
<li>Pull 2-1B (v) with med lab (v).<br />
<li>Deploy any chars/ships that it is safe do to so</ul><br />
<br />
<b>3rd Turn</b><br />
<br />
<ul>Complete your setup. This might involve pulling your final piece of generation with ANSB, putting haven on hoth or putting delevar at the med lab for more ground protection. Most games you will end turn 3 with a jedi at the 4th marker and a ship or two at hoth.</ul><br />
Now, what does all massive downloading get you? Here&#39;s the text for the less common cards:<br />
<br />
<i>General McQuarrie</i><br />
While McQuarrie is on Hoth, your Hoth sentry is not unique (), is doubled, deploys free, applies all three of its modifiers and is immune to alter. Power -1 when not on Hoth.<br />
<br />
<i>Hoth Sentry</i><br />
Use 2 Force to deploy at any Hoth site. Declare one of the following to affect that site and adjacent sites while &#39;sentry&#39; present: opponent&#39;s deploy +1. OR Opponent&#39;s ability required for battle destiny +1. OR Your total power +1.<br />
<br />
<i>Corporal Delevar</i><br />
Prevents your characters from having their forfeit reduced at same location (and at Hoth sites if Delevar is at Echo Med Lab). When with your FX droid, once per turn allows your character just forfeited from same site to be placed in Used Pile.<br />
<br />
<i>2-1B (v)</i><br />
Once per turn, your non-droid character lost at same or related site may go to your Used Pile instead of your Lost Pile. Subtracts 2 from X on your Bacta Tank.<br />
<br />
<i>Tigran Jamiro (v)</i><br />
Deploys free to Dantooine, Yavin 4 or Hoth. Opponent&#39;s aliens and Imperials deploy +1 to same and related sites.<br />
<br />
So this is what you have when you&#39;re set up. Generation of 12-14 (depending on endor shield(v)) which is 100% pullable, immune to WTO(v) and gives up only 3 icons. Your opponent&#39;s imperials/aliens deploy +3 (vehicles/droids +2) to 3rd/4th marker, your total power is +4 at hoth system and +3 at 3rd/4th marker (remember, rieken (v) at war room gives +1) and your opponent needs 6 ability to draw destiny at 3rd/4th marker (this is great vs mara (v)). Your fleet deploys for next to nothing and adds a battle destiny at hoth. Movement from Rendezvous point to your Endor is free, so you can get ships there very cheaply too. You potentially drain for 3 at both hoth and Endor, 2 at 3rd marker (you want to move either McQuarrie or Tigran over to do this), and 1+lightsaber bonuses at 4th marker. Your characters at hoth sites can&#39;t have their forefit reduced and both them and their weapons go to used pile if lost.<br />
<br />
So with all this, the deck does well against decks which want to invade your sites (eg. hunt down, bhbm). The +2/3 deploy is huge. Lord vader is 11. EPP maul/mara (v) 9. Boba, BH 8. So if you&#39;ve got Luke, RS (v) down at the 4th marker they need 12 force just to drop EPP maul, initiate and swing twice. They will never be able to drop more than vader/maul and a support character and have enough force left for weapon/battle destinies. And when they do, they&#39;re not going to do much damage to you, thanks to what&#39;s at your med lab. You are quite safe in leaving a lone jedi at the 4th marker.<br />
<br />
For all that, this deck has some obvious weaknesses:<br />
<ul><li>Massive card inefficiency. You have a huge number of cards on the table, so you will lose any tit-for-tat drain race.<br />
<li>No retrieval. Well, except weapons display (v) which you can set up reasonably often. I wanted to use the first transport is away but the reduxed bright hope (v) doesn&#39;t deploy/move like a starfighter :(. Destiny isn&#39;t good enough for OTE and I got no room to combine it with flash (v).<br />
<li>Drop (v). You will usually give 2-3 drop (v) pulls in the first 2 turns and 1 for a turn or 2 after that. If you have the grimtaash combo in hand early, this can work to your advantage if they&#39;re silly enough to draw more than 12. But there&#39;s really no point in going slower, you activate a lot quite quickly so if you hold off downloading things like sai&#39;tor you&#39;ll never find them.<br />
<li>Force saving. In between Obi, JK (v), quick draw (v), bright hope (v) and meditation (v) you&#39;ll often have 3 or more force sitting in your force pile for a number of turns. It can be very annoying.</ul><br />
And some things which look like weaknesses, but probably aren&#39;t:<br />
<ul><li>J&#39;Quille (v). She could mess around with chars at echo sites but far as I can tell everyone replaced her with Mara (v) so she&#39;s not as much of a threat as she used to be.<br />
<li>Elis beats. Look under the starting effect :). Meditation (v) should be a high priority pull with We Wish to Board<br />
<li>KTOD-senate. They kick you out of space and so you can&#39;t do anything on the ground. That&#39;s why scrambled transmission is there - it turns an auto-loss into a contest.</ul><br />
<br />
So it&#39;s not tier 1, I&#39;ll freely admit that, but it is a fun deck with some unusual tech in it, I think.<br />
<br />
Finally, 61st card:<br />
<ul><li>Bacta tank. There&#39;s 2 cards here which subtract 2 from X and redemption (v) even makes it deploy for free. There was just no room, though, and it wasn&#39;t getting used often enough with 2-1B recycling anyway.<br />
<li>2nd alter. For Fear and luke luke(v). Just no room.<br />
<li>Goo. +5 deploy is eeeevill. But it didn&#39;t get out quickly often enough to make a difference.</ul>  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/starwarsccg/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=3610e0b36c8d368fda0b2a64bf9bb1db">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/starwarsccg/decks/decks.php?reviews=35670&PHPSESSID=3610e0b36c8d368fda0b2a64bf9bb1db"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=35670&PHPSESSID=3610e0b36c8d368fda0b2a64bf9bb1db" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/starwarsccg/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=3610e0b36c8d368fda0b2a64bf9bb1db">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table>
